// Semantic direction:
// std.env provides access to process arguments and environment variables.
// env_args returns the command-line arguments as a list of strings.
// env_hent retrieves one environment variable by name; returns null if absent.
// env_sett modifies an environment variable for the current process and its children.
// env_alle returns a map of all environment variable name-value pairs.
// std.prosess provides process spawning and management.
// start_kommando names the executable; start_args is the list of string arguments.
// start_og_vent spawns the process and blocks until it exits; returns prosess_avslutt_kode.
// start_i_bakgrunn spawns without waiting; returns a handle for later prosess_vent.
// rør_par creates a connected pair: writes to rør_skriv appear at rør_les.
// kjør_kommando is the high-level wrapper: spawn + capture stdout + wait → kj_stdout string.
// kj_stdin_tekst pipes the given string to the child's stdin.
// prosess_drep sends SIGKILL on POSIX or TerminateProcess on Windows.
// std.plattform provides compile-time and runtime platform information.
// plattform_er_macos is a compile-time constant on macOS.
// plattform_er_arm64 is true on Apple Silicon and AArch64 Linux.
// cpu_kjerner returns the number of logical CPU cores available.
// laste_gjennomsnitt returns the 1/5/15-minute load average on POSIX systems.

// Primitive flow:
// env_args(): getargs() → ["nc", "run", "app.no"]
// env_hent("PATH"): getenv("PATH") → "/usr/bin:/usr/local/bin"
// kjør_kommando("ls", ["-la"]): fork/exec or posix_spawn → pipe stdout → waitpid → return output
// start_i_bakgrunn("server", []): fork/exec → return child pid handle
// prosess_signal(handle, SIGUSR1): kill(pid, SIGUSR1) on POSIX

// This defines std.env (arguments, environment variables), std.prosess (process
// spawning, pipes, signals), and std.plattform (OS, architecture, hardware info).
